// -----------------------------------------------------------------
// Outbound send helper — posts to the PulseBoard HTTP API.
// In a real implementation this would call:
//   fetch(`${account.serverUrl}/api/dm/<target>`, { method: "POST",
//     headers: { Authorization: `Bearer ${account.apiKey}` },
//     body: JSON.stringify({ text }) })
// for DMs, and the boards endpoint for board messages.
//
// Inbound message dispatch follows these patterns (wired up by the
// real PulseBoard WebSocket/long-polling client, not shown here since
// PulseBoard is a fictional protocol):
//
//   Direct messages → dispatchInboundDirectDmWithRuntime({
//     peer: { kind: "direct", id: senderId }, ... })
//     after resolveInboundDirectDmAccessWithRuntime / authorizeDmSender.
//
//   Board messages  → runtime.channel.routing.resolveAgentRoute({
//     peer: { kind: "group", id: boardId } }), then
//     runtime.channel.reply.finalizeInboundContext({ ChatType: "group", ... })
//     and runtime.channel.reply.dispatchReplyWithBufferedBlockDispatcher({...}).
//     (A dedicated dispatchInboundBoardWithRuntime helper would live in
//     openclaw/plugin-sdk/pulseboard once the plugin has a full SDK facade.)
// -----------------------------------------------------------------

